<dec f='linux-5.3.1/include/rdma/ib_verbs.h' l='2849' type='bool ib_modify_qp_is_ok(enum ib_qp_state cur_state, enum ib_qp_state next_state, enum ib_qp_type type, enum ib_qp_attr_mask mask)'/>
<doc f='linux-5.3.1/include/rdma/ib_verbs.h' l='2834'>/**
 * ib_modify_qp_is_ok - Check that the supplied attribute mask
 * contains all required attributes and no attributes not allowed for
 * the given QP state transition.
 * @cur_state: Current QP state
 * @next_state: Next QP state
 * @type: QP type
 * @mask: Mask of supplied QP attributes
 *
 * This function is a helper function that a low-level driver&apos;s
 * modify_qp method can use to validate the consumer&apos;s input.  It
 * checks that cur_state and next_state are valid QP states, that a
 * transition from cur_state to next_state is allowed by the IB spec,
 * and that the attribute mask supplied is allowed for the transition.
 */</doc>
